MT. CARMEL COGEN, INC. REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION OR OTHER SOURCES SERVICE
Mt. Carmel Cogen, Inc. ("MCC") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation or Other Sources Service ("Reactive Service") from an electric generation facility located near Mount Carmel, Pennsylvania ("Facility") that is interconnected to the transmission system operated by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM"). This Reactive Service Tariff sets forth MCC's revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Service from the Facility pursuant to Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff, which provides for PJM to pay generation owners their monthly revenue requirements for Reactive Service.
Total charges for any 12-month period will not be less than the annual charges specified below. This Reactive Service Tariff shall be effective on August 1, 2016.
REACTIVE SERVICE REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
TOTAL REVENUE REQUIREMENT
The total annual revenue requirement is $124,872.00. The total monthly revenue requirement is $124,872.00 / 12 = $10,406.00.
